metadata.name: Felicien Rops
metadata.description:
Felicien Victor Joseph Rops was a Belgian artist associated with Symbolism and the Parisian Fin-de Siecle. He was a painter, illustrator, caricaturist and a prolific and innovative print maker, particularly in intaglio. Rops was greatly respected by his peers and actively pursued and celebrated as an illustrator by the publishers, authors, and poets of his time and provided frontispieces and illustrations for Jules Barbey, Charles Baudelaire, Charles De Coster, Theophile Gautier, Joris-Karl Huysmans, Stephane Mallarme, Josephin Peladan, Paul Verlaine, Voltaire, and many others. 

Art historians do not consider Rops a seminal figure of late 19th century art, even among the symbolists, and yet no credible review of symbolism could ignore him either. Some of his critics dismiss him as a novel, 19th-century illustrator/pornographer, but others look beyond the erotica and write of him respectfully and favorably.

Jean-Luc Daval spoke of "the amazing upsurge of Symbolism that in the wake of Felicien Rops and under the influence of Gustave Moreau, characterised Belgian painting at the turn of the century."

metadata.name: Dueling Banjos
metadata.description:
Dueling banjos is a period-24 oscillator found (in tetramer form, via apgsearch) by Apple Bottom on January 10, 2019. It consists of two B-heptominos being hassled by two eater 1s and two block on tables.

Matthias Merzenich provided a monomer form which has cis-in, cis-out and trans isomers depending on the relative positions of the two blocks.

Mark Niemiec posted a 19-glider synthesis of the oscillator on January 13th.

metadata.name: Last Lines
metadata.description:
How many lines have been drawn on fxhash since that first generative logo started growing on a Wednesday in early November? How many brush strokes, wires, cables, threads? Many thousands per mint? Millions per project? Billions in total? Shall we add just a few more to celebrate the end of the genesis? Here are 222 iterations with 111 lines each. Each line connects two edges of the canvas but may get deflected by hidden attractors in an attempt to minimize friction and deviation from its path.

Press [p]rint to save a high resolution capture.

This artwork is fully generative and was entirely hand-coded in 4,400 characters of plain JavaScript. Forever limited to 222 editions on the Tezos blockchain. I hope you will enjoy yours. London, March 2022.

metadata.name: Rings
metadata.description:
Rings is the cummulative texturized generative artwork obtained after several animations of a determinated number of particles seeking a concentric pattern in several rings. But in this case, to get some different results of depth and texture, the chosen particles weregeometrical 2D shapes (like lines, circles, squares and triangles). Also, white 1D dots with low stroke in a descentralized radius from pattern center brings a nice highlighting effect, helping the depth feeling.
All the codes were developed and studyed for a quite time, and after a high number of tests and modifications I believe Rings is ready to be yours!

Its a big pleasure be back :)

And again....palletes carefully chosen.

See the features! Ranking system set up!

Press 's' to save canvas.
Nice experience at full view.

metadata.name: Soragna
metadata.description:
Soragna is an abstract generative series reproducing the effect of paint strokes.
The fundamental element of this system is an object composed of two lines which oscillate perpendicular to the direction of movement. A little like a bird flapping its wings, each element moves on the canvas, leaving behind it the imprint of its passage.

Variability of editions is ensured by:
- 18 color palettes (including 4 rare)
- possibility to combine 2 different palettes
- Constrained directions of the field
- Field symmetries
- Speed, size and size variability of "birds"


To save as a png file, press the following keys:
- [1] for a 2400x4000 pixel image
- [2] for a 4800x8000 pixel image
- [3] for a 7200x12000 pixel image

The image must be recalculated before the chosen dimension can be downloaded. The wait is worth it.



Note regarding the symbolism of the series:

I thought it was interesting to publish this series to celebrate the end of the fxhash beta. The artists on fxhash are like these birds leaving behind them the trace of their passage on the site. Their paths are sometimes parallel, they can cross and even sometimes come together to produce unique collaborations.

Thank you to all the artists and collectors for making the last few months an incredible journey! The best is still to come ...

Artist: Estienne
March 2022
License: NFT 2.0

metadata.name: Back to the Roots
metadata.description:
It is hard to imagine our everyday life without electronic circuits - they are inside coffee machines we use in the morning, cars that drive us to work, and phones we stare into for the rest of the day. 

Without them, millions of things we know and love wouldn't be possible. And one of those things is, quite frankly, our beloved generative art. 

And if art can't exist without circuits, it makes sense to immortalize them inside of art. So let's make out journey back to what made it possible in the first place.. back to the roots.

made in p5.js
credit for the algo base goes to Michael Lowe
twt: @p1neaqp1e

metadata.name: A New Dawn

Black pyres, their greedy fingers cracked and blistered.
The light of twin suns, pouring blindly into space.
A memory of grass, of days of sun—
—a blue hose held askance—
the flare of new light dawning over cracked and unsmoothed hands.

metadata.name: Phaces
metadata.description:
Faces + Phases = Phaces. A living artwork celebrating variety and community, with a healthy dose of delayed gratification.

Each Phace starts in black and white, a simple but fascinating look at the variety that can emerge from a few lines of code. It is a sober start to an exciting journey and a reminder that good things take time.

Each week, your Phace evolves. You’ll see the next evolution every Saturday for 12 weeks, providing moments for the collector community to come together to share and celebrate the latest Phaces – there will be some wild ones in there!

Each Phace has a name, generated from a list of 144 adjectives and a 144 names randomly selected from the US census. Other features hint at the exciting evolutions to come. You know that Nonchalant Erma with Palette = Electric and Colour Boost = Wild is going to be up for a party. 

We won’t say much more, for risk of spoiling the surprises but we can’t wait to see your Phaces emerge and evolve over these coming weeks. Follow along for updates on Twitter, Insta and at https://www.phaust.art/.

------

Edition Size: 156. A tribute to the inspiration and evolution of fxHash over the 156 day beta. 

Palettes: Azure, Bioluminant, Day Glo, Electric, Lava Lamp, Livid, Peach, Peacock, Powder, Retro, Royal, Turple.

Evolutions: 12.

S: to save current Phace. All saves are at high resolution.
G: to save a grid of all revealed Phaces.
1-9, 0, E, T: to save a specific Phace – one to nine, then ten, eleven and twelve.

Each Phace has a name, generated from a list of 144 adjectives and a 144 names randomly selected from the US census. Other features hint at the exciting evolutions to come. You know that Nonchalant Erma with Palette = Electric and Colour Boost = Wild is going to be up for a party. 

We won’t say much more, for risk of spoiling the surprises but we can’t wait to see your Phaces emerge and evolve over these coming weeks. Follow along for updates on Twitter, Insta and at https://www.phaust.art/.

------

Edition Size: 156. A tribute to the inspiration and evolution of fxHash over the 156 day beta. 

Palettes: Azure, Bioluminant, Day Glo, Electric, Lava Lamp, Livid, Peach, Peacock, Powder, Retro, Royal, Turple.

Evolutions: 12.

S: to save current Phace. All saves are at high resolution.
G: to save a grid of all revealed Phaces.
1-9, 0, E, T: to save a specific Phace – one to nine, then ten, eleven and twelve.

metadata.name: Alien Blobs
metadata.description:
It is said that were we to encounter life elsewhere in the universe, it may come in a form that is completely unfamiliar to us here on Earth.  This generative token creates structures which resemble alien blobs flying their environment.  Perhaps they live in some atmospheric anomaly of a planet, or perhaps they simply represent the strangeness of possible life out there in the unknown. Regardless, they do fly up unsettlingly for a few seconds before the token settles on the final image for that viewscreen size.  Larger viewscreen is recommended to see a more biological feel to it.  The collectible features of this NFT are: 

ColorScheme: red-purple (common), orange-yellow (common), purple (~10%), red (~10%)
ShapeScheme: tall (~10%), wide (~5%), circle (common) 

the ColorScheme and ShapeScheme determine dominant overall features in the tokens having those features.
